
#
# Fiend of Blasphemy


Blood Oath			KEY:Fiend of Blasphemy ~ Blood Oath			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Blasphemy Class Feature			DESC:The ability to perform an initiation ritual that binds cult members to a fiend's service. The ritual requires one uninterrupted day to prepare, lasts 2 hours, plus an additional 10 minutes per mortal initiate. Resisting the ritual requires a DC %1 Will save (DC 15 + fiend's class level + CHA).|(15 + (CL=Fiend of Blasphemy) + CHA)
Locate Cultist			KEY:Fiend of Blasphemy ~ Locate Cultist			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Blasphemy Class Feature			DESC:At will a Fiend of Blasphemy can use a supernatural power identical to Locate Creature to sense the location of any creature that has sworn a blood oath to the fiend.
Undetectable Alignment		KEY:Fiend of Blasphemy ~ Undetectable Alignment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Blasphemy Class Feature			DESC:A Fiend of Blasphemy's alignment is constantly concealed from all forms of divination, as the Undetectable Alignment spell.
Transfer Spell-like Ability	KEY:Fiend of Blasphemy ~ Transfer Spell-like Ability	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Blasphemy Class Feature			DESC:A Fiend of Blasphemy can transfer any of its spell-like abilities to a Blood Oath bound cultist. All variable properties of the ability remain as if the fiend invoked the ability. Any transferred ability counts against the fiend's daily usage count. This transferance can be revoked as a free action.
Sponsor Worshiper		KEY:Fiend of Blasphemy ~ Sponsor Worshiper		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Blasphemy Class Feature			DESC:A Fiend of Blasphemy can channel power from its own master to a cultist. A find can sponsor a Cleric twice the Fiend of Blasphemy's own class level with a full compliment of spells and access to any two domains offer by the fiend's master.
Scry on Cultist			KEY:Fiend of Blasphemy ~ Scry on Cultist		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Blasphemy Class Feature			DESC:Once per day a Fiend of Blasphemy can scry upon each Blood Oath bound cultist as if using the Scry spell unless the cultist is on another plane.
Torture Cultist			KEY:Fiend of Blasphemy ~ Torture Cultist		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Blasphemy Class Feature			DESC:A Fiend of Blasphemy can inflict pain upon any Blood Oath bound cultist who is on the same plane as the fiend. The cultist suffers a -4 penalty on attack rolls, skill checks, and ability checks for %1 rounds. A DC %2 (DC 10 + fiend's class level + CHA) reduces this penalty to -2.|(CL=Fiend of Blasphemy)|(10 + (CL=Fiend of Blasphemy) + CHA)
Mind Shielding			KEY:Fiend of Blasphemy ~ Mind Shielding			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Blasphemy Class Feature			DESC:Immunity to Detect Thoughts and Discern Lies spells.
Kill Cultist			KEY:Fiend of Blasphemy ~ Kill Cultist			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Blasphemy Class Feature			DESC:A Fiend of Blasphemy can kill any Blood Oath bound cultist who is on the same plane as the fiend. The cultist must save against this death effect, DC %1 (DC 10 + fiend's class level + CHA) or die. A successful save still causes the cultist to take 3d6+6 points of damage.|(10 + (CL=Fiend of Blasphemy) + CHA)

#
# Fiend of Corruption

Alternate Form		KEY:Fiend of Corruption ~ Alternate Form		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Corruption Class Feature		DESC:A Fiend of Corruption has the ability to assume any humanoid form of Small to Large size as a standard action. This ability is similar to the Polymorph Self spell but allows only humanoid forms. While using this ability, the fiend gains a +10 circumstance bonus on Disguise checks.
Fiend's Favor		KEY:Fiend of Corruption ~ Fiend's Favor			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Corruption Class Feature		DESC:Once per day, a Fiend of Corruption can grant a touched creature a +3 bonus to one of the creature's ability scores. This bonus stacks with any other bonus the creature may already have, and lasts for one day. When the effect expires the creature takes a -3 penalty to the same ability score for the next day. Another application of the Fiend's favor not only negats the penalty, but restores the full bonus.
Suggestion		KEY:Fiend of Corruption ~ Suggestion			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Corruption Class Feature	SPELLS:Class|TIMES=3|CASTERLEVEL=FoCLVL|Suggestion,(15+CHA)	DESC:At 2nd level, a Fiend of Corruption gains the ability to use Suggestion DC %1 3/day. If the taret of this ability is currently under the influence of a Charm Person spell cast by the Fiend, they take a -2 penalty on their save.|(15 + CHA)
Mind Shielding		KEY:Fiend of Corruption ~ Mind Shielding		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Corruption Class Feature		DESC:At 2nd level, a Fiend of Corruption gains complete immunity to Detect Thoughts, Discern Lies, and any attempt to magically discern its alignment.
Mark of Iniquity	KEY:Fiend of Corruption ~ Mark of Iniquity		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Corruption Class Feature	SPELLS:Class|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=FoCLVL|Mark of Justice		DESC:At 3rd level, a Fiend of Corruption can cast Mark of Justice 1/day.
Fiendish Graft		KEY:Fiend of Corruption ~ Fiendish Graft		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Corruption Class Feature		DESC:Once per month, a Fiend of Corruption of 4th level or higher can bestow a fiendish graft or symbiont on a willing mortal.
Major Creation		KEY:Fiend of Corruption ~ Major Creation		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Corruption Class Feature	SPELLS:Class|TIMES=3|CASTERLEVEL=FoCLVL|Major Creation			DESC:A 4th level Fiend of Corruption gains the ability to cast Major Creation 3/day.
Geas			KEY:Fiend of Corruption ~ Geas				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Corruption Class Feature	SPELLS:Class|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=FoCLVL|Geas/Quest			DESC:At 5th level, a Fiend of Corruption can cast Geas 1/day.
Temptation		KEY:Fiend of Corruption ~ Temptation			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Corruption Class Feature		DESC:At 5th level, a Fiend of Corruption gains the ability to offer good creatures the opportunity to change their alignment to evil. This works like the redemption or temptation function of the Atonement spell.
Grant Wish		KEY:Fiend of Corruption ~ Grant Wish			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Corruption Class Feature	SPELLS:Class|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=FoCLVL|Wish			DESC:A 6th level Fiend of Corruption can grant a Wish to a mortal (not an elemental, outsider, or nonliving creature) 1/day. When using this ability the Fiend incurs the XP cost as if it were casting a Wish spell.
Soul Bargain		KEY:Fiend of Corruption ~ Soul Bargain			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Corruption Class Feature		DESC:At 6th leel, a Fiend of Corruption gains the ability to enter a binding agreement with a mortal, at the cost of the mortal's soul. The mortal victim must enter into the Soul Bargain willingly, wherein after an hour-long effort the mortal's soul is transfer to a gem (which needn't even be on the same plane as the mortal). The only way to undo their bargain is to recover the gem and destroy it.

#
# Fiend of Possession

Ethereal Form		KEY:Fiend of Possession ~ Ethereal Form		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Possession Class Feature	SPELLS:Class|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=max(if((CL=Sorcerer)>0, ((CL=Sorcerer) + FoPLVL), 0), TL)|Etherealness		DESC:At will, a Fiend of Possession can become ethereal, as though using the Etherealness.
Hide Presence		KEY:Fiend of Possession ~ Hide Presence		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Possession Class Feature		DESC:A Fiend in possession of an object or creature can attempt to hide its presence by making a special Hide check using the Fiend's Intelligence modifier instead of its Dexterity modifier. A successful check allows a Fiend of Possession to avoid virtually anything that would betray its presence in the possessed creature or object; it can pass through a Magic Circle against Evil, enter a temple warded by Forbiddance, or escape detection via Detect Evil. The Hide DC is the same as the saving throw DC. The Fiend gains a +4 circumstance bonus on this check if it is not controlling the possessed creature or object at the time of the check. See text for additional details.
Possess Object		KEY:Fiend of Possession ~ Possess Object	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Possession Class Feature		DESC:A Fiend of Possesssion in ethereal form can possess an object on the Material Plane. The object must be at least Tiny and no larger than Huge. Magic items and attended items receive Will saves (DC %1) and unattended nonmagical items are automatically possessed. See text for additional details.|FoPPossessionDC
Curse			KEY:Fiend of Possession ~ Curse			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Possession Class Feature		DESC:At 2nd level, a Fiend of Possession gains the ability to make a possessed item radiate a corrupt and befouling nature. Anyone touching the object must make a Will save or fall under the effect of a Bestow Curse spell.
Magic Item		KEY:Fiend of Possession ~ Magic Item		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Possession Class Feature		DESC:At 2nd level, a Fiend of Possession gains the ability to make a possessed weapon or armor function as a magic item. The Fiend can bestow powers on a nonmagical, or enhance an existing magical, item with a value as an enhancement bonus of up to its class level (ex. a 3rd level Fiend can make a nonmagical sword a +3 weapon, a +2 keen weapon, or a +1 wounding weapon or make an existing +1 weapon a +1 speed weapon, or a +1 frost icy bursting weapon). Nonmagical items granted powers in this way do not detect as magic but they do detect as evil. See text for additional details.
Control Object		KEY:Fiend of Possession ~ Control Object	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Possession Class Feature		DESC:When possessing an object with some inherent mobility, a Fiend of Posession can control the objects movement. Exerting control is a free action, though actually moving an object requires a move action.
Animate Object		KEY:Fiend of Possession ~ Animate Object	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Possession Class Feature		DESC:At 4th level, a Fiend of Possession gains the ability to force an object with no inherent moving parts to animate, effectively animating it as with an Animate Object spell. At this level, a Fiend of Possession can also possess and animate Gargantuan objects.
Possess Creature	KEY:Fiend of Possession ~ Possess Creature	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Possession Class Feature		DESC:At 4th level, a Fiend of Possession gains the ability to possess creatures. The Fiend must be in ethereal form and adjacent to its target, and must use a standard action to attempt possession. A Protection from Evil spell or similar magic wards a creature against being possessed in this manner. An unprotected target must make a Will save (DC %1), evil creatures take a -2 penalty on this save, as do creatures that are engaged in an evil act. If the save is successful that creature is immune to that Fiend's attempts for one day. A failed save means the creature is possessed through they might not necessarily be aware of this fact.|FoPPossessionDC
Ally or Enemy		KEY:Fiend of Possession ~ Ally or Enemy		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Possession Class Feature		DESC:At 5th level, a Fiend of Possession can, as a free action, grant a +4 profane bonus or a -4 profane penalty to one ability score of the creature it possesses.
Possess Noncontinuous Object		KEY:Fiend of Possession ~ Possess Noncontinuous Object		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Possession Class Feature		DESC:At 5th level, a Fiend of Possession can use its possess object ability to take control of an "object" more loosely defined (ex: a pool of water, a cloud of dust, or a section of wall or floor). At this level, a Fiend can possess and animate Colossal objects.
Control Creature	KEY:Fiend of Possession ~ Control Creature	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Fiend of Possession Class Feature		DESC:At 6th level, a Fiend of Possession gains the ability to exert direct control over a creature it is possessing. Attempting to establish control is a standard action for the Fiend. The victim must make a Will save (DC %1) each round until the Fiend abandons the attempt, or the victim fails the save giving the Fiend control. Once the Fiend gains control, it automatically maintains it for a number of rounds (Fiend of Possession level + CHA + 1 for each previous successfully controlled occassions).|FoPPossessionDC




